 The Lagos State Police Command have arrested 43 suspected members of a notorious gang known as “No Salary’’. The gang, made up of young boys and girls, had been terrorising residents of Ikotun in Lagos for some time now. Police Public Relations Officer of the command, DSP Bala Elkana, who made the disclosure in a chat with the News Agency of Nigeria on Thursday, said that nine locally made pistols were recovered from the suspects. He said, “Operation Crush arrested 43 ‘no salary’ boys over the last few days and recovered nine locally made pistols. “The operations will continue until they are totally uprooted.”